Sent: Sunday, July 30, 2023 10:45 AM
To: claims <claims@canadageneral.ca>
Subject: 2019 Durango 5th wheel
 
We have a 2019 Durango 5th wheel 2500 343 mbq. We have had issues with it since we bought it in 2021.we bought it new in March 27/2021. Didnt receive till may at which time the 2 year KZ warranty started. We paid for the extended warranty when we bought it, was an extended 5 year warranty for $2249. I have all my documents in hand if needing pictures. VIN# 4EZFD3428K6042040 . THE DEALER IN WHICH WE BOUGHT THE 5TH WHEEL WAS ROBINSON RV, Get Hitched out of Fergus Ontario, 519-993-6304
  The main issue I'm getting in touch with you is our main slide issue which we had repaired by the dealer in fall of  2022, during the 2 year manufacturing warranty.  After the 1st trip of 2023 their repairs failed. Their solution is to retape the problem area. The floor in the main slide went rotten, I'm guessing while it sat on their lot cause wood doesn't rot in a few months. Between Robinson and KZ their Solution was to only replace what was rotten and tape over the outside. The tape has come off, pulled away and is now exposing the wood repairs.  The dealer,Robinson has kind of wiped their hands clean of it and said they would re tape if I wanted them to. Re taping would last for another trip with it and be torn off again. I think so far I'm the only one who sees this. They directed me to KZ directly. Their only response was re tape it, and re-align tour slide. The dealer claims they can't do this
There has to be something else. That slide should have been replaced when I asked for it. There is other issues wrong with this 5th wheel that seems to be not getting fixed by dealer ,front Door won't latch right from Inside and now won't lock, electric fireplace hasn't worked from day 1,I think all the slides should be adjusted, front right landing gear or stability jacks needs a hammer to move since day 1. I guess me and my wife are now dealing with you guys on our issues, I don't understand why but I guess that's why we bought the 5 year extended warranty. I've attached some pictures the 1st 2 I think is the after "repair" the last one is the before. And also attached is a pic of my bill of sale. Thanks, also I would like to not take this trailer back to Robinson rv. I do not think they know what they are doing. I have a decent dealer up the road ,I think they would be worth you paying to have these repairs done
Sent from my Bell Samsung device over Canada’s largest network.
